President Obama spoke with Prime Minister Erdogan of Turkey to discuss developments in Syria, particularly the regime's use of chemical weapons against its own people. They both expressed their commitment to finding a political solution and discussed the need for more support to the Syrian Coalition and the Supreme Military Council to enhance their effectiveness. They also emphasized the importance of close cooperation between the two countries in contingency planning and counterterrorism efforts. Prime Minister Erdogan also briefed President Obama on the situation in Turkey, and they both emphasized the importance of nonviolence, free expression, assembly, and press freedom.